        <h1 class="news-title">New "Attack on Titan" Movie Announced — Set to Expand the Manga's Ending!</h1>
        <img src="banner2.svg" alt="banner" class="news-image">
        <p class="news-text">
            The story of *Attack on Titan* continues in a new way — Studio MAPPA has announced a full-length animated movie
            that will expand the original ending of the manga. The news broke during a live-streamed anniversary event.
            <br><br>
            The film is set to explore untold stories and deeper lore surrounding the Titans and Eldians.
            Key staff from the anime series will return, ensuring visual and narrative consistency.
            A theatrical release is planned for summer 2026.
            <br><br>
            "We want to give closure in the most powerful way possible," said director Yuichiro Hayashi.
            Fans are already speculating about alternative endings teased in early visuals. Could this change everything we know?
        </p>

